name: Launcher One
description: LauncherOne is a two-stage orbital launch vehicle under development by Virgin Orbit since 2007. It is an air-launched rocket, designed to carry small satellite payloads of up to 300 kilograms (660 lb) into Sun-synchronous orbit (SSO), following air launch from a carrier aircraft at high altitude. The rocket was first launched to space on 17 January 2021.

name: AIM54A Phoenix
description: The AIM-54 Phoenix is a radar-guided, long-range air-to-air missile (AAM), carried in clusters of up to six missiles on the Grumman F-14 Tomcat
